  ('glenn-dale-hospital', 'Glenn Dale Hospital', 'Glenn Dale', '5500 Glenn Dale Road', 'MD', 38.9867, -76.8206, 'hospital', 'Built in 1934 during the tuberculosis epidemic, this sanatorium once comprised 23 buildings before closing in 1981 due to asbestos. Added to the National Register of Historic Places in 2011, it remains abandoned and haunted.', 'The Goatman of Maryland, a half-man half-goat creature, allegedly haunts the grounds. A large pack of ghost dogs roams the property. Ghostly patients wander the second floor, and smoke rises from the long-cold crematorium. Banging, yelling, screams, and laughter come from the walls. The morgue deep inside the main building is a paranormal hotspot.', 1934, 'https://www.hauntedplaces.org/item/glenn-dale-hospital/');

